    <h1>Computers for Beginners</h1>
    
    <p>Welcome to your first step in learning about computers! A computer is an electronic device that processes information, performs calculations, and stores data.</p>

    <h2>Basic Components of a Computer</h2>
    
    <p><strong>1. Hardware:</strong> The physical parts of a computer, including the keyboard, mouse, monitor, and internal components like the processor and memory.</p>
    <p><strong>2. Software:</strong> Programs and applications that run on a computer, like a web browser or word processor.</p>
    
    <h2>How Computers Work</h2>
    
    <p>Computers take input, process it, store data, and produce output. They follow instructions given by software to complete tasks.</p>

    <h2>Why Learn About Computers?</h2>
    
    <p>Computers are essential in everyday lifeâ€”helping with communication, work, entertainment, and learning new skills.</p>
    
    <p>Enjoy your journey into the world of computing!</p>

